OL,5, Energy companies have been granted     
OL,6, approval to resume force-fitting       
OL,7, prepayment meters in people's homes    
OL,8, nearly a year after it was suspended.  
OL,10,FEDF, Octopus and Scottish Power can    
OL,11,Finstall the meters again after meeting 
OL,12,Fvarious requirements set by Ofgem, the 
OL,13,Findustry regulator.                    
OL,15,FFor years, energy companies were able  
OL,16,Fto force-fit meters into homes when    
OL,17,Fbills went unpaid.                     
OL,19,FBut agents for British Gas were exposed
OL,20,Finstalling them inappropriately.       
